The paper deals with the complexity of no-signaling proofs, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). It also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of communication complexity, as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) in the context of approximating the value of sub-no-signaling games. The paper's results are also related to learning theory (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT), as it involves analyzing the behavior of multiple players in a game.
